About
Home
»
About
The Art League was founded in 1989 by a small group of artists and art lovers with a desire to promote art to the island community. The League has offered a broad range of classes, including a scholarship program for children and adults.  A Women’s Wellness Weekend program was developed to learn about the intersection of wellness and art.
The league has also been involved in promoting public art, such as the mural at the Island Branch Library in Holmes Beach.
Annually the League sponsors a juried fine arts and fine crafts festival, Springfest, that provide funds for the League and its scholarship fund.
Classes and Workshops
Coming soon, updates on classes and workshops.

Membership
Home
»
Membership
Join or renew your membership with the Anna Maria Island Art League. Membership supports the arts in our community and we are dreaming up new ways to engage.
Discounts on classes and workshops
Link from the Island Art League website
On-line Member Gallery
Get Membership
Be a Gem and show your support of the arts with a patron level membership.
You receive all the benefits of Basic Membership plus our most grateful recognition of you, Our Gem, in the Art League newsletter, on the Sponsor page of our website, and recognition at exhibits.
Two Ways to Become  A Member
Membership fees are paid annually, and partial years are pro-rated.
Purchase Online
Basic: $15.00 – $45.00
Select Options
Gem: $100 – $5,000
Select Options
Send By Mail
Print and mail the membership application with your check to:
Anna Maria Island Art League Inc
PO Box 1243,
Holmes Beach, FL 34218
